    {
      "@type": "Project",
      "schema:legalName": "Ischia Dolphin Project",
      "schema:name": "Ischia Dolphin Project",
      "schema:url": "https://www.oceanomaredelphis.org/progetto-ischia-dolphin-project/",
      "schema:description": "The study area is located in the central Tyrrhenian Sea (Italy) and extends for about 8800 km2; it includes the Campanian Archipelago (Gulf of Naples, islands of Ischia, Procida, Capri) and the Pontine Archipelago (Gulf of Gaeta, islands of Ventotene and Ponza) both located on the eastern Tyrrhenian continental margin.\r\nThe main aim of the project is to identify key areas for cetaceans . Other goals are:\r\n\r\nestimate the degree of residence of cetaceans around Ischia;\r\nestimate the size and trend of populations;\r\nstudy the social structure of populations;\r\nstudy the use of the environment and the distribution in the area;\r\nestimate the impact on animals of fishing operations and vessel traffic;\r\ndescribe the acoustic repertoire of cetaceans.\r\n\r\nIn addition to purely scientific objectives, the study project aims at the protection of cetaceans through:\r\n\r\nraising awareness of public opinion on the problems of cetaceans and the environment in which they live;\r\nthe communication of the results obtained to local and international authorities, and to environmental organizations;\r\nthe protection of the area.\r\n",
